    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> Firestar99 submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13319#pullrequestreview-4247065253\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 593606900,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778181622
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> Firestar99 created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13319#discussion_r3204124687\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>While in the front end (ast and sema) I added a separate struct variant everywhere, when it proceeds to adding rules and match statements, I start reusing enum's variants by making the <code>VariantId</code> optional everywhere. This is the only place where anything actually matches on it, which allows my code changes to be quite minimal in this area.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 593606902,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778181622
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> cfallin submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13319#pullrequestreview-4247068339\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks! This is a nice extension of ISLE and will certainly make it more useful in binding to other environments.</p>\n<p>A few thoughts on the data-structure design below. Overall shape (reusing <code>enum</code>'s code as much as possible) seems right, though.</p>\n<p>Also cc @mmcloughlin / @avanhatt as they have some (not-yet-upstreamed) additions to ISLE and will probably want to be aware of this.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 593607900,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778181939
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13319#discussion_r3204136651\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>LIkewise here -- let's model the domain a bit more closely.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 593607902,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778181940
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13319#discussion_r3204132624\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Likewise here, let's not overload the meaning of <code>Some</code>/<code>None</code> in a somewhat ad-hoc way. Maybe we should have a <code>StructOrEnumVariant</code> enum, take that here, and use that in the <code>EnumVariant</code> enum arm above?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 593607903,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778181940
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13319#discussion_r3204127532\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Rather than overload <code>EnumVariant</code> here and give it no inner information for structs, let's add a <code>Struct</code> TermKind.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 593607904,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778181940
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13319#discussion_r3204139536\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If we separate out the struct case here, why do we make the variant IDs <code>Option</code>s above?</p>\n</blockquote>",
