        "content": "<p>Firestar99 edited <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13319\">PR #13319</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I have a code generator that creates rust code similar to this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IAdd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">WriteableReg</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Reg</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Reg</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IConst</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">WriteableReg</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">imm</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Imm</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">enum</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MInst</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">IAdd</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">IAdd</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">IConst</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">IConst</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I would like to modify my code generator to also emit isle that matches this particular style of codegen. But isle only supports enums, so this PR adds support for structs: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Common Lisp\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">IAdd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">struct</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">out</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">WriteableReg</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">Reg</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">Reg</span><span class=\"p\">)))</span>\n<span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">IConst</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">struct</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">out</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">WriteableReg</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">imm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">Imm</span><span class=\"p\">)))</span>\n<span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">MInst</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">enum</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">IAdd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">IAdd</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">IConst</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">IConst</span><span class=\"p\">))))</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is not quite sufficient to properly map it this example, as isle doesn't support tuple-like enum variants. But that can be a follow up PR some other day.</p>\n<p><strong>Also</strong> changes the temp directory for isle link and run tests to <code>./target/tmp/&lt;test-name&gt;/</code>. Using system tmp and deleting it regardless of test failure makes it hard to debug broken rust code emissions.</p>\n</blockquote>",
